  volume    = {19},
  abstract  = {A hypothesized underlying principle of the diversity-functioning relationship is that functional groups respond differently
to environmental change. Over 3 years, we investigated how pollinator diversity contributes to the magnitude
of pollination service through spatial complementarity and differential response to high winds in California
almond orchards. We found honey bees preferentially visited the top sections of the tree. Where wild pollinators were
