  abstract  = {Recent reviews of plant-pollinator mutualistic networks showed that generalization
is a common pattern in this type of interaction. Here we examine the ecological
correlates of generalization patterns in plant-pollinator networks, especially how interaction
patterns covary with latitude, elevation, and insularity. We review the few published analyses
