  url       = {http://www.esajournals.org/doi/abs/10.1890/13-0436.1},
  abstract  = {Land use is known to reduce the diversity of species and complexity of biotic
interactions. In theory, interaction networks can be used to predict the sensitivity of species
against co-extinction, but this has rarely been applied to real ecosystems facing variable landuse
impacts. We investigated plant-pollinator networks on 119 grasslands that varied
