  number    = {3},
  pages     = {829--836},
  volume    = {52},
  abstract  = {(1) Experiments using honey bees and artificial flower patches were designed to test three alternative foraging ecology models: optimal diet, minimal uncertainty, and individual constancy. Honey bee responses to a mixed colour flower patch and to flower morph associated differences in reward quantity, quality, and frequency were measured. 
(2) Each honey bee visiting a patch of randomly distributed blue and yellow flowers was constant to one colour, even though that behaviour was suboptimal. 
